Do that!

00:01:25.250 --> 00:01:28.360
As beginners, let's make sure we're holding
our airbrush properly

00:01:28.360 --> 00:01:31.560
and make sure when you do this line, that
you're double actioning.

00:01:31.560 --> 00:01:34.970
Double action, so we know we're doing it right.

00:01:34.970 --> 00:01:39.850
the process of doing a line correctly;
air down,

00:01:39.850 --> 00:01:42.880
pull back for paint..
and move with your body.

00:01:42.880 --> 00:01:47.020
Then repeat that process in reverse
stop moving with your body,

00:01:47.020 --> 00:01:50.480
Push forward to cut off paint..
and only then can you release the air.

00:01:50.480 --> 00:01:55.010
Make sure when you paint this line, that you're
distancing correctly.

00:01:55.010 --> 00:01:56.830
What is distancing?

00:01:56.830 --> 00:02:01.800
Distancing is when you use the opposite hand
from the hand you airbrush with,

00:02:01.800 --> 00:02:04.650
to maintain a distance from your artwork.

00:02:04.650 --> 00:02:09.369
So for example I'm right handed,
I'll use my left hand for distancing.

00:02:09.369 --> 00:02:13.200
Holding the airbrush,
maintain a distance from the artwork.

00:02:13.200 --> 00:02:17.060
The reason for this is so that we get a nice
uniform line -

00:02:17.060 --> 00:02:21.620
It shouldn't go from small, to big to small.

00:02:21.620 --> 00:02:24.750
That's not even a straight line.

00:02:24.750 --> 00:02:26.350
I'll distance with my left hand,
start moving,

00:02:26.350 --> 00:02:27.350
pull back for paint.

00:02:27.350 --> 00:02:28.510
Paints off,
stop moving,

00:02:28.510 --> 00:02:31.230
air off.

00:02:31.230 --> 00:02:41.310
Let's do it again and see if we can create
exactly the same line.

00:02:41.310 --> 00:02:48.400
Let's go in a little bit closer and see what
happens when we're about 5cm from the paper.

00:02:48.400 --> 00:02:49.400
Ha!

00:02:49.400 --> 00:02:51.360
The line gets smaller!

00:02:51.360 --> 00:02:55.560
Let's see what happens when we go in at two
centimetres!

00:02:55.560 --> 00:02:59.110
The lines are getting smaller!

00:02:59.110 --> 00:03:05.920
So why don't try pulling back less on the
paint?

00:03:05.920 --> 00:03:11.360
Our lines are getting smaller again.

00:03:11.360 --> 00:03:13.740
but why are you teaching me this??

00:03:13.740 --> 00:03:18.190
Just draw something!
the detailed areas of your artworks, such

00:03:18.190 --> 00:03:21.480
as here in the eye,
mean that you have to move extremely close

00:03:21.480 --> 00:03:25.740
to the artwork,
and it also means, that you have to pull back

00:03:25.740 --> 00:03:27.870
very little for paint.

00:03:27.870 --> 00:03:33.000
Let's see what happens when we distance, 20cm
from the paper.

00:03:33.000 --> 00:03:34.000
Ha!

00:03:34.000 --> 00:03:35.000
The line's bigger!

00:03:35.000 --> 00:03:39.530
The further away you are from the artwork,
the thicker your lines are going to be.

00:03:39.530 --> 00:03:43.450
the more you pull back, the thicker your lines
are going to be.

00:03:43.450 --> 00:03:50.340
applying less paint at a closer distance,
will mean you get finer detailed lines.

00:03:50.340 --> 00:03:59.010
I want to get better,
How can i get better?

00:03:59.010 --> 00:04:02.599
If you want to improve, then practise this
little exercise;

00:04:02.599 --> 00:04:04.970
I want you to do two dots.

00:04:04.970 --> 00:04:10.560
Now i want you to practise doing a line that
starts on the very middle of one dot,

00:04:10.560 --> 00:04:13.630
and ends on the very middle of the next dot.

00:04:13.630 --> 00:04:16.621
Remember this;
Whenever you're doing a line - snap on, snap

00:04:16.621 --> 00:04:22.680
off!

00:04:22.680 --> 00:04:32.110
